<script type="text/javascript">
    function setExecutor(execFile, execArgs) {
        document.querySelector('.executor-input').value = execFile;
        document.querySelector('.executor-args-input').value = execArgs;
        return false;
    }
</script>
The command that executes your script. It must have at least a <a target="_blank" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.diagnostics.processstartinfo.filename">filename</a>, and optionally some <a target="_blank" href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.diagnostics.processstartinfo.arguments">arguments</a>.
<br /><br />
If <code>{0}</code> is present in the arguments field, it is replaced with the script file path. Otherwise, the path is appended at the end.
<div class="mt-3">
    <div class="small text-muted mb-1">Cross-platform</div>
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-1 mb-3">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" onclick="return setExecutor('/usr/bin/env', 'bash -c')">Bash</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" onclick="return setExecutor('/usr/bin/env', 'bash -l -c')">Bash (login shell)</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" onclick="return setExecutor('/usr/bin/env', 'pwsh -NonInteractive -f')">PowerShell (Core)</button>
    </div>
    <div class="small text-muted mb-1">Windows only</div>
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-1">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" onclick="return setExecutor('C:\\Program Files\\Git\\bin\\bash.exe', '-c &quot;exec $(cygpath -u \'{0}\')&quot;')">Git Bash</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" onclick="return setExecutor('cmd.exe', '/C')">cmd.exe</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary" onclick="return setExecutor('powershell.exe', '-NonInteractive -f')">Windows PowerShell</button>
    </div>
</div>
